![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8e7a31fc-3a4b-488e-9a0b-1e1c7289e499/Screenshot+2026-01-14+010520.png)

This week on the **Major Issues Podcast**, the hosts break down **Absolute Universe 101**, a crash course on DC’s bold new publishing initiative. From its core concepts and creative goals to how it reimagines iconic characters and continuity, this episode serves as an entry point for readers curious about what makes the Absolute Universe different from DC’s traditional canon.

The discussion covers what you need to know going in, which titles are essential reading, and whether this new universe feels like a fresh start or just another reinvention. It is a beginner-friendly guide to one of DC’s most ambitious recent experiments.

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**iTunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters. Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise. All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

